        "title": "Harden autoreview bundle generation",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- harden Git bundle collection with isolated config, explicit ref validation, no implicit fetch, safe diff flags, and NUL-delimited path parsing\n- reject sensitive, secret-like, symlinked, outside-repository, or unsafe untracked/evidence inputs while bounding text reads\n- sanitize reviewer subprocess environments without removing current Codex, Claude, Droid, Pi, OpenCode, or Copilot isolation\n- expose Copilot web fetching only when web search is enabled\n\n## Compatibility\n\n- current reviewer engines, model defaults, and web-search defaults remain unchanged\n- `--prompt-file` and `--dataset` now require repository-relative files\n- branch review requires the selected base ref to exist locally\n\n## Validation\n\n- `python3 -m py_compile skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview skills/autoreview/tests/test_autoreview_hardening.py`\n- `python3 -m unittest skills.autoreview.tests.test_autoreview_hardening` (11 tests)\n- `scripts/validate-skills`\n- `skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --self-test-engine-isolation`\n- `skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --self-test-config-defaults`\n- `skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --self-test-fallback-scope`\n- structured Codex autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\nThe original hardening commit was ported onto current `main` rather than merging its stale helper implementation over newer reviewer-isolation work.\n",
